OL,3,CFamilies 'very anxious' for relatives
OL,4,Cin Bangladesh as unrest continues
OL,6,FFamilies in Wales have spoken of their
OL,7,Fanxiety and concern over the safety of
OL,8,Frelatives and friends still living in
OL,9,FBangladesh.
OL,11,FAround 300 people are thought to have
OL,12,Fdied in the South Asian country since
OL,13,Fprotests began in July. The
OL,14,Fdemonstrations started as student
OL,15,Fprotests but quickly spread, prompting
OL,16,Fa government ordered crackdown.
OL,18,FIt has left members of the Bangladeshi
OL,19,Fcommunity here in Wales worried about
OL,20,Fwhat might happen to those caught up
OL,21,Fin the disruption, 5,000 miles away.
